Sentencas: The sulfur resistance and regeneration ability of Ni- or Co-impregnated La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-delta (LSCrM) composite anodes are investigated in this study.
Titulo: Sulfur poisoning and the regeneration of the solid oxide fuel cell with metal catalyst-impregnated La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-δ anode

Sentencas: The sulfur resistance of the composite anodes are assessed after a 5 h sulfur poisoning process.
Titulo: Sulfur poisoning and the regeneration of the solid oxide fuel cell with metal catalyst-impregnated La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-δ anode

Sentencas: Interestingly, the composite anodes exhibit weak sulfur resistance due to the excellent catalytic activity of catalyst to fuel oxidation.
Titulo: Sulfur poisoning and the regeneration of the solid oxide fuel cell with metal catalyst-impregnated La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-δ anode

Sentencas: Both chemical and electrochemical oxidative methods are attempted to realize the regeneration of the composite solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) after the sulfur poisoning process.
Titulo: Sulfur poisoning and the regeneration of the solid oxide fuel cell with metal catalyst-impregnated La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-δ anode

Sentencas: Notably, opposite results are exhibited by the two regeneration methods for the composite SOFCs.
Titulo: Sulfur poisoning and the regeneration of the solid oxide fuel cell with metal catalyst-impregnated La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-δ anode

Sentencas: The chemical oxidative method can restore the electrochemical properties of the composite SOFCs, but the electrochemical oxidative method cannot.
Titulo: Sulfur poisoning and the regeneration of the solid oxide fuel cell with metal catalyst-impregnated La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-δ anode

Sentencas: The regeneration and failure mechanisms of the Ni- or Co-impregnated LSCrM anodes are evaluated in detail.
Titulo: Sulfur poisoning and the regeneration of the solid oxide fuel cell with metal catalyst-impregnated La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3-δ anode
